result.execSummary:
The defendant Rodolfo Martinez was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes:
Court Costs to be paid as a Condition of Probation at the rate of $75.00 per month starting 08-01-2015; alternate 4 days Jail.  Defendant may use Community Service in Lieu of fine at $10.00 equals 1 hour.  Defendant may go to W.C.S. for information on Community Service.

If probation is revoked and a prison term is not ordered, or if probation is discharged/terminated, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant and in favor of restitution victims and government entities for outstanding financial obligations.  Collection may include income assignment.
AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended.

Maintain ABSOLUTE SOBRIETY.
No use or possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.
No use or possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription.
Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed.
Inform Agent of all prescriptions.
Sign any/all Medical Releases for Agent.
Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent.
No contact with:  victim (defendant's son) or his residence unless the victim and residents at the resident, consent is given and Agent agrees to contact.
Operate a motor vehicle with a valid driver's license.
Defendant to obtain a driver's license within the First 9 months of Probation.
Compete an Anger Management Program.
